the energy density in stable neutrinos:
Ωνh2{\textless}0.0072 (95\% confidence limit).
For three degenerate neutrino species, this limit implies that their
mass is less than 0.23 eV (95\% confidence limit). The WMAP detection of
early reionization rules out warm dark matter.

WMAP is the result of a partnership between Princeton University and the
NASA Goddard Space Flight Center. Scientific guidance is provided by the
WMAP Science Team.},
